{"image_id": "WDC_2012_page_79", "image_size": [1238, 1613], "ocr": [{"text": "WESTERN DIGITAL CORPORATION", "bbox": [426.1, 139.8, 811.7, 160.6]}, {"text": "NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS — (Continued)", "bbox": [237.3, 177.3, 1000.7, 198.2]}, {"text": "Fair Value Disclosure — Binomial Model", "bbox": [164.6, 228.2, 475.0, 249.1]}, {"text": "The fair value of stock options granted is estimated using a binomial option-pricing model. The binomial model", "bbox": [185.5, 265.8, 1094.1, 286.6]}, {"text": "requires the input of highly subjective assumptions including the expected stock price volatility, the expected price", "bbox": [143.8, 290.8, 1094.1, 311.6]}, {"text": "multiple at which employees are likely to exercise stock options and the expected employee termination rate. The", "bbox": [143.8, 315.8, 1094.2, 336.7]}, {"text": "Company uses historical data to estimate option exercise, employee termination, and expected stock price volatility", "bbox": [143.8, 340.8, 1093.9, 361.7]}, {"text": "within the binomial model. The risk-free rate for periods within the contractual life of the option is based on the", "bbox": [143.8, 365.8, 1094.1, 386.7]}, {"text": "U.S. Treasury yield curve in effect at the time of grant. The fair value of stock options granted during the three years", "bbox": [143.8, 390.8, 1094.0, 411.7]}, {"text": "ended June 29, 2012 was estimated using the following weighted average assumptions:", "bbox": [143.8, 415.8, 843.5, 436.7]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [637.2, 448.1, 670.6, 464.8]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [802.9, 448.1, 836.3, 464.8]}, {"text": "2010", "bbox": [968.6, 448.1, 1002.0, 464.8]}, {"text": "Suboptimal exercise factor . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 482.5, 565.9, 503.4]}, {"text": "1.81", "bbox": [635.7, 482.5, 672.1, 503.4]}, {"text": "1.81", "bbox": [801.4, 482.5, 837.8, 503.4]}, {"text": "1.73", "bbox": [967.1, 482.5, 1003.5, 503.4]}, {"text": "Range of risk-free interest rates . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 513.8, 565.9, 534.6]}, {"text": "0.12% to 1.61%", "bbox": [586.7, 513.8, 721.1, 534.6]}, {"text": "0.20% to 2.90%", "bbox": [752.4, 513.8, 886.8, 534.6]}, {"text": "0.31% to 3.40%", "bbox": [918.1, 513.8, 1052.5, 534.6]}, {"text": "Range of expected stock price volatility . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 545.1, 565.9, 565.9]}, {"text": "0.41 to 0.55", "bbox": [604.1, 545.1, 703.7, 565.9]}, {"text": "0.39 to 0.59", "bbox": [769.8, 545.1, 869.4, 565.9]}, {"text": "0.40 to 0.72", "bbox": [935.5, 545.1, 1035.1, 565.9]}, {"text": "Weighted average expected volatility . . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 576.3, 565.9, 597.2]}, {"text": "0.49", "bbox": [635.7, 576.3, 672.1, 597.2]}, {"text": "0.52", "bbox": [801.4, 576.3, 837.8, 597.2]}, {"text": "0.57", "bbox": [967.1, 576.3, 1003.5, 597.2]}, {"text": "Post-vesting termination rate . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 607.6, 565.9, 628.4]}, {"text": "2.61%", "bbox": [626.9, 607.6, 680.8, 628.4]}, {"text": "2.44%", "bbox": [792.6, 607.6, 846.4, 628.4]}, {"text": "3.57%", "bbox": [958.3, 607.6, 1012.1, 628.4]}, {"text": "Dividend yield . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 638.8, 565.9, 659.7]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [643.5, 638.8, 664.3, 659.7]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [809.2, 638.8, 830.0, 659.7]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [974.9, 638.8, 995.7, 659.7]}, {"text": "Fair value . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [185.5, 670.1, 565.9, 690.9]}, {"text": "$12.91", "bbox": [625.3, 670.1, 682.6, 690.9]}, {"text": "$11.42", "bbox": [790.9, 670.1, 848.3, 690.9]}, {"text": "$17.09", "bbox": [956.6, 670.1, 1014.0, 690.9]}, {"text": "The weighted average expected term of the Company’s stock options granted during 2012, 2011 and 2010 was", "bbox": [185.5, 707.6, 1094.2, 728.4]}, {"text": "4.9 years, 4.7 years and 4.6 years, respectively.", "bbox": [143.8, 732.6, 515.3, 753.5]}, {"text": "Fair Value Disclosure — Black-Scholes-Merton Model", "bbox": [164.6, 782.6, 564.6, 803.4]}, {"text": "The fair value of ESPP purchase rights issued is estimated at the date of grant of the purchase rights using the", "bbox": [185.5, 820.1, 1094.1, 841.0]}, {"text": "Black-Scholes-Merton option-pricing model. The Black-Scholes-Merton option-pricing model was developed for use", "bbox": [143.8, 845.1, 1094.1, 866.0]}, {"text": "in estimating the fair value of traded options that have no vesting restrictions and are fully transferable. The Black-", "bbox": [143.8, 870.2, 1094.1, 891.0]}, {"text": "Scholes-Merton option-pricing model requires the input of highly subjective assumptions such as the expected stock", "bbox": [143.8, 895.2, 1094.1, 916.0]}, {"text": "price volatility and the expected period until options are exercised. Purchase rights under the current ESPP provisions", "bbox": [143.8, 920.2, 1093.9, 941.0]}, {"text": "are granted on either June 1st or December 1st of each year.", "bbox": [143.8, 945.2, 622.9, 966.0]}, {"text": "The fair values of all ESPP purchase rights granted on or prior to June 29, 2012 have been estimated at the date", "bbox": [185.5, 982.7, 1094.1, 1003.5]}, {"text": "of grant using a Black-Scholes-Merton option-pricing model with the following weighted average assumptions:", "bbox": [143.8, 1007.7, 1036.4, 1028.5]}, {"text": "ESPP", "bbox": [968.3, 1040.0, 1006.3, 1056.7]}, {"text": "2012", "bbox": [887.3, 1062.9, 920.7, 1079.6]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [965.5, 1062.9, 998.8, 1079.6]}, {"text": "2010", "bbox": [1048.9, 1062.9, 1082.2, 1079.6]}, {"text": "Option life (in years) . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .", "bbox": [143.8, 1095.2, 859.7, 1116.1]}, {"text": "1.24", "bbox": [891.0, 1095.2, 927.5, 1116.1]}, {"text": "1.25", "bbox": [969.1, 1095.2, 1005.6, 1116.1]}, {"text": "1.24", "bbox": [1057.7, 1095.2, 1094.2, 1116.1]}, {"text": "Risk-free interest rate . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .